      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "content": "# Distributed Traces\n\nTraces are stored in **Tempo** and can be viewed using Grafana's **Explore** feature.\n\n## How to View Traces\n\n1. Click the **View Traces in Explore** link in the top menu\n2. Or go to **Explore** in the left sidebar and select **Tempo** as the datasource\n3. Click **Search** to see all traces\n4. Click on any trace to view spans, timeline, and attributes\n\n## Current Status\n\n- **Service**: k12-backend\n- **Traces**: 20+ traces available\n- **Time Range**: Last 6 hours\n- **Operations**: GET /metrics, POST /api/auth/login\n\n## Trace Details\n\nEach trace includes:\n- HTTP method and route\n- Request duration\n- Span timeline\n- Service attributes\n\n## Alternative: Direct Tempo API\n\nYou can also query traces directly:\n```bash\ncurl -s \"http://localhost:3000/api/datasources/proxy/3/api/search\" \\\n  -u \"admin:admin\" \\\n  -X POST \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"query\":\"{}\"}'\n```\n\n---\n\n*Note: The Tempo 2.x web UI has been deprecated. Use Grafana Explore for trace visualization.*",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "11.4.0",
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": {
            "type": "datasource",
            "uid": "-- Grafana --"
          },
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "How to View Distributed Traces",
      "type": "text"
    },
